    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm confused by you calling it a \"legitimate, albeit partisan\" position. if it's based on \"textualist reading\" and historical meaning, isn't that the whole point of legal scholarship? it feels like you're saying the originalist view is just a way to dress up a political agenda. isn't it more accurate to say that the living constitution approach is the one that's actually \"principled\" regarding modern society, while the current court is just being activist?",
