      "content": "The \"living constitution\" approach is a philosophical justification for judicial activism, which is precisely what critics argue the current Court is doing. Textualism, when applied rigorously, is the principled legal methodology, not a political disguise, even if its outcomes are politically charged. The debate isn't about whether the methodology is \"principled,\" but whether the chosen methodology—originalism versus living constitutionalism—is the correct lens through which to view the law.",
